      static interface  ValueFactory.BoundedValueBuilder<E>
      A builder pattern for constructing MutableBoundedValues without the hassle of keeping track of the order of arguments.

      • createOptionalValue

        <E> OptionalValue<E> createOptionalValue(Key<OptionalValue<E>> key,
                                         @Nullable
                                         E element)
        Creates an OptionalValue where even the default value may be Optional.empty(). These types of values should be restricted to values that are live, that can be potentially large to retain a reference to, and otherwise, not thread safe.
        Type Parameters:
        E - The type of element
        Parameters:
        key - The key to the value
        element - The element, if available
        Returns:
        The newly created value
